Hello Sumod,

Except for special cases, to solve x^3 + y^3 = 3*a*x*y for either x or y involves solving a 
cubic equation.  For the known methods for solving cubics, see


http://mathforum.org/dr.math/faq/faq.cubic.equations.html


- Doctor Jerry, The Math Forum
